{"id": "1490800581898539240", "channel_id": "1326453691527594035", "author_id": "274853543934951425", "author_name": "morgaenrei", "content": "I will go on a rant.\n\nI would encourage exploration of comps if there was a fun and creative element to be found in it. Alas, the nature of any game is that players tend to \"optimize\" all the fun out it. Meta comps are simply more consistent in their chances of winning, because they rely on hard synergy, that has been already proven by other players. It doesn't mean they are not fun to play. And since the entire balance of this mode revolves around specifically 2 things: knowledge and accuracy of your plays (means you have to screw up less times than your enemy did), there is like no room for any experimentation. There is a set path, and if you deviate from it - you lose. \"Uneven exchanges\" is the only creative random element in the fights, but again - they also rely on your knowledge of the effects and know-how to use them most efficiently. The most matchups are also tend to be even in chances of winning, but... at one point or the other you gonna be thrown against hard meta comps, and unless you know your comp as the back of your palm you can almost forget about winning any of those. \n\nTLDR: The choice is false. There is an always objectively better path to win a fight. MY advice is to accept the meta and learn it. After that try to figure out your own like KaDe.", "timestamp": "2026-04-06T19:49:16.460000+00:00", "reactions": [{"emoji": "🔥", "emoji_id": null, "count": 1}]}
